.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1374:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:60:Phases were delivered in strict dependency order: runtime truth first, then coverage graph, then wave execution, then offline optimization. The original four phases were independently validated against their task lists and quality gates.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1375:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:65:- **Phase 006 — graph testing and playbook alignment.** Added vitest coverage across the coverage-graph layers and authored matching playbook scenarios so manual QA mirrors the automated checks.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1376:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:22:Phase 003 adds orchestrator-managed parallel wave execution so deep research and deep review can handle very large targets without abandoning the LEAF-worker model. It formalizes deterministic segmentation, packet-local coordination, segment-level convergence, and auditable merge behavior on top of the coverage-graph foundation from Phase 002.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1377:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:39:| **Predecessor** | `../002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md` |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1378:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:44:**Phase Context**: This phase adds orchestrator-managed parallel batches on top of the coverage-graph substrate from Phase 002. The goal is scale without architectural drift: the workers stay LEAF, while orchestration logic handles segmentation, fan-out, pruning, promotion, and merge.
