e/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:357:    upsertNode(makeResearchNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'research-question', 'QUESTION', 'Research question'));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5545:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:358:    upsertNode(makeResearchNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'research-finding-a', 'FINDING', 'Research finding A'));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5546:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:359:    upsertNode(makeResearchNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'research-finding-b', 'FINDING', 'Research finding B'));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5547:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:364:      sessionId,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5548:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:371:    upsertNode(makeReviewNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'review-dimension', 'DIMENSION', 'Correctness'));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5549:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:372:    upsertNode(makeReviewNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'review-file', 'FILE', 'coverage-graph.ts', { hotspot_score: 2 }));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5550:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:373:    upsertNode(makeReviewNode(specFolder, sessionId, 'review-finding', 'FINDING', 'Review finding'));\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5551:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-cross-layer.vitest.ts:378:      sessionId,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5574:Description: `insertEdge()` synthesizes missing nodes without any `sessionId`, but every session-aware reader/filter only trusts `node.sessionId` or `node.metadata.sessionId`. That means a caller can build a graph entirely through the public insert API, attach `metadata.sessionId` to edges, and still lose those nodes from `getNodes()` and any signal helper that depends on node-level session matching. This makes the session-aware export surface easy to misuse and hard to reason about.  \\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5581:sessionId: typeof metadata.sessionId === 'string' && metadata.sessionId ? metadata.sessionId : undefined,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5584:if (typeof node.sessionId === 'string' && node.sessionId) return node.sessionId;\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5586:if (matchesSession(graph, node, sessionId, 'node')) results.push(node);\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5588:Recommendation: Centralize graph/session normalization in one shared helper and either propagate `metadata.sessionId` into synthesized nodes or add an explicit node upsert API. Add direct session-scoped tests for `getNodes()`, `getEdges()`, `getEdgesFrom()`, `getEdgesTo()`, and the signal helpers.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5596:Description: The CJS helper exports `computeMomentum(graph, nodeId, windowSize, sessionId)` as a recent-edge counter, while the canonical runtime implementation exports `computeMomentum(specFolder, loopType)` as a snapshot-to-snapshot delta calculator in [.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:555). Same name, different meaning. That is a long-term drift trap for maintainers, especially because the requested test suite only validates the CJS behavior in [.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-signals.vitest.ts](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-signals.vitest.ts:117).  \\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5600:function computeMomentum(graph, nodeId, windowSize, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5641:function reportContradictions(graph, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5647:function contradictionDensity(graph, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5681:Description: `insertEdge()` synthesizes missing nodes without any `sessionId`, but every session-aware reader/filter only trusts `node.sessionId` or `node.metadata.sessionId`. That means a caller can build a graph entirely through the public insert API, attach `metadata.sessionId` to edges, and still lose those nodes from `getNodes()` and any signal helper that depends on node-level session matching. This makes the session-aware export surface easy to misuse and hard to reason about.  \\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5688:sessionId: typeof metadata.sessionId === 'string' && metadata.sessionId ? metadata.sessionId : undefined,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5691:if (typeof node.sessionId === 'string' && node.sessionId) return node.sessionId;\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5693:if (matchesSession(graph, node, sessionId, 'node')) results.push(node);\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5695:Recommendation: Centralize graph/session normalization in one shared helper and either propagate `metadata.sessionId` into synthesized nodes or add an explicit node upsert API. Add direct session-scoped tests for `getNodes()`, `getEdges()`, `getEdgesFrom()`, `getEdgesTo()`, and the signal helpers.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5703:Description: The CJS helper exports `computeMomentum(graph, nodeId, windowSize, sessionId)` as a recent-edge counter, while the canonical runtime implementation exports `computeMomentum(specFolder, loopType)` as a snapshot-to-snapshot delta calculator in [.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:555). Same name, different meaning. That is a long-term drift trap for maintainers, especially because the requested test suite only validates the CJS behavior in [.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-signals.vitest.ts](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/coverage-graph-signals.vitest.ts:117).  \\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5707:function computeMomentum(graph, nodeId, windowSize, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5748:function reportContradictions(graph, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:5754:function contradictionDensity(graph, sessionId) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:3:description: \\\"Four-phase implementation delivering runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across 100 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research and sk-deep-review.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:60:Phases were delivered in strict dependency order: runtime truth first, then coverage graph, then wave execution, then offline optimization. The original four phases were independently validated against their task lists and quality gates.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:71:1. **Lane 1 — Claim-Adjudication Stop Gate Wiring** closed F002 and F007 by adding a universal STOP veto pre-check and a dedicated `claimAdjudicationGate` in the review legal-stop decision tree, plus persisted `claim_adjudication` events, typed packet docs in `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md` §9, and matching `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/loop_protocol.md` §Step 4a. New REQs: REQ-026, REQ-027.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:72:2. **Lane 2 — Coverage-Graph Session Isolation** closed F004, F005, F006, and F013 by bumping `deep-loop-graph.sqlite` to v2 with a composite primary key of `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` on both `coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges`, migrating via drop-and-recreate, adding a shared-ID collisions regression to `session-isolation.vitest.ts`, and documenting the typed `graphEvents` payload shape and namespace rules in both state_format references. New REQs: REQ-028, REQ-029.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:75:5. **Lane 5 — Release-Readiness Reconciliation** closed F013, F014, F015, and F016 by rewriting the phase-008 closeout surfaces, the packet-root completion surfaces below, and the reducer-owned `ACTIVE RISKS` dashboard section so non-P0 release-readiness debt stays visible. New REQ: REQ-034.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:114:| Closing-audit Lane 1–5 remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034) | PASS — see `008-further-deep-loop-improvements/implementation-summary.md` §Closing Audit Remediation Notes and `review/review-report.md` |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:42:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"D3: Is the mutation coverage graph namespace (`loop_type: \\\\\\\"improvement\\\\\\\"`) properly isolated from the deep-research/deep-review namespaces in the shared SQLite store?\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:72:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"D5: Does any loop phase (init / iteration / convergence / synthesis) actively READ from the coverage graph (`coverage-graph-query.ts`, `coverage-graph-convergence.cjs`) to inform decisions, or only WRITE to it?\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:90:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"D5: Does the coverage graph's contribution to the 3-signal convergence math exceed its weight, or is it merely nominal?\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:301:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"`sk-improve-agent` follows a different path entirely: its resume contract replays a local \\\\\\\"coverage graph + registry\\\\\\\", and `mutation-coverage.cjs` persists an `improvement` JSON graph with `fs`/`path` helpers and `loopType: 'improvement'`, while the agent only consumes an orchestrator-provided summary as advisory context. That means it does not supply the missing shared `deep_loop_graph_*` bridge for research/review convergence (.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:294-300; .opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs:9-10; .opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs:21; .opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs:50-67; .opencode/agents/agent-improver.md:175-177).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:319:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Both deep-loop convergence contracts still document a reducer-owned in-memory graph bridge that is not present in the live reducer: deep research says \\\\\\\"the reducer builds an in-memory coverage graph\\\\\\\" when `graphEvents` exist, and deep review says the same for review iterations (.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1181-1205; .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/convergence.md:658-683).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:711:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The published deep-research contract says that when `graphEvents` exist, \\\\\\\"the reducer builds an in-memory coverage graph and derives additional signals for the legal-stop gate evaluation,\\\\\\\" including graph coverage sub-checks (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md:1181-1205`). The live research reducer does not implement that bridge: its only imports are `fs` and `path`, and its convergence score is taken from `latestIteration.convergenceSignals?.compositeStop` or `latestIteration?.newInfoRatio` rather than any graph helper (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:11-13`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:244-249`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1177:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The resume contract promises richer recovery than the shipped journal helpers provide. The skill says resume replays the journal, coverage graph, and registry before dispatch, but the journal module only exposes raw-event readback, `getLastIteration()`, and `getSessionResult()`. If an interruption happens before a `session_ended` event is written, `getSessionResult()` returns `{ stopReason: null, sessionOutcome: null }`, so the helper surface itself does not reconstruct candidate, gate, benchmark, or trade-off state (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:290-300`, `.opencode/commands/improve/agent.md:332-339`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/improvement-journal.cjs:148-203`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1263:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The published resume contract promises more reconstruction than the shipped recovery helper exposes. Both the command and skill say resume replays the journal, coverage graph, and registry before dispatch, but the only recovery-facing journal helpers return the max iteration number and the terminal `stopReason/sessionOutcome`; there is no helper that rebuilds blocked-stop payloads, trade-off state, benchmark warnings, or lineage context from raw journal events (`.opencode/commands/improve/agent.md:334-339`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:290-295`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/improvement-journal.cjs:168-203`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1530:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The shipped deep-review reducer mirrors the same pattern. `computeConvergenceScore()` reads `latest.convergenceSignals.compositeStop` or falls back to `1 - newFindingsRatio`, and the reducer then publishes only that scalar as `convergenceScore`. No inspected review reducer code reconstructs a coverage graph or invokes graph convergence logic before writing the dashboard/registry (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:360-390`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:579-583`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:671-680`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1551:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The standalone graph helper does have bounded weight, not runaway influence: `computeGraphConvergence()` builds `graphScore` from fragmentation (0.25), normalized depth (0.25), question coverage (0.30), and source diversity (0.20), then limits the merged result to `blendedScore = compositeStop * 0.6 + graphScore * 0.4`. Inside this helper, the coverage graph cannot contribute more than 40% of the final blended scalar (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/coverage-graph-convergence.cjs:141-205`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1735:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"A different namespace-isolation weakness does exist on the shared read side for research/review sessions: the convergence handler never accepts `sessionId`, constructs its namespace from only `{ specFolder, loopType }`, and then calls `getStats()` plus `computeSignals()` / `computeMomentum()` without session scoping, so convergence decisions aggregate all sessions sharing the same spec folder and loop type (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:47-52`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:92-111`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:511-545`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-signals.ts:163-220`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1779:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The published `sk-improve-agent` contract and visible auto workflow keep that mutation coverage graph local to the improvement runtime rather than bridging it into the shared coverage-graph MCP. The skill describes `scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs` as the reader/writer for the coverage graph and says it uses `loop_type: \\\\\\\"improvement\\\\\\\"` isolation, while the auto workflow only appends the state ledger and runs `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`; I found no visible `deep_loop_graph_upsert` step on this path (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:298-300`, `.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:389-390`, `.opencode/commands/improve/assets/improve_agent-improver_auto.yaml:149-155`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1801:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The query surface only partially exposes session isolation. `handleCoverageGraphQuery()` accepts `sessionId` and passes it into `ns`, but the inspected helper queries for coverage gaps, contradictions, and unverified claims read by `spec_folder` and `loop_type` only, ignoring `ns.sessionId`; this means research/review sessions can be co-mingled on read even though improvement-mode entries are blocked from the DB entirely (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:28-35`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:55-58`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts:63-126`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts:136-147`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-query.ts:238-277`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:1823:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"The shared SQLite coverage graph does not admit `improvement` loop types at all. The DB layer defines `LoopType = 'research' | 'review'`, constrains valid kinds/relations by those two namespaces, and the schema enforces `CHECK(loop_type IN ('research', 'review'))`; the MCP upsert handler repeats the same validation and rejects any other value (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:17`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:136-146`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:152-157`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts:51-53`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts:72-80`).\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2121:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"`SKILL.md` says resume replays the journal, coverage graph, and registry before dispatch and that the orchestrator skips mutation types already in the exhausted log, but the visible autonomous loop never invokes `mutation-coverage.cjs` before candidate generation. The shipped loop proceeds from integration scan directly to candidate generation, scoring, benchmarking, ledger append, reducer refresh, and reducer-driven stop check, so coverage state does not visibly steer mutation focus selection. (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:294-300`, `.opencode/commands/improve/assets/improve_agent-improver_auto.yaml:137-158`)\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2513:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"I did not find a shipped orchestrator implementation file that performs the promised “replay journal + coverage graph + registry before dispatch,” so this pass had to prove absence via reducer inputs and helper interfaces rather than a single end-to-end resume driver.\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/findings-registry.json:2558:      \\\"text\\\": \\\"A command-doc requirement to invoke structural graph tools before or during iterations; the inspected command surfaces only bootstrap CocoIndex.\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:130:### Dashboard-only ancestry surfacing: The review reducer/dashboard still show only `sessionId`, `lineageMode`, and `generation`, but without a live restart/fork/completed-continue write path this stayed downstream of F010 rather than a distinct release-level defect. -- BLOCKED (iteration 5, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:131:- What was tried: Dashboard-only ancestry surfacing: The review reducer/dashboard still show only `sessionId`, `lineageMode`, and `generation`, but without a live restart/fork/completed-continue write path this stayed downstream of F010 rather than a distinct release-level defect.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:133:- Do NOT retry: Dashboard-only ancestry surfacing: The review reducer/dashboard still show only `sessionId`, `lineageMode`, and `generation`, but without a live restart/fork/completed-continue write path this stayed downstream of F010 rather than a distinct release-level defect.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:160:### Handler fallback without `sessionId`: The `all_sessions_default` path is explicitly documented bootstrap/debug behavior rather than a hidden bypass — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:70`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:174`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/status.ts:71` -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:161:- What was tried: Handler fallback without `sessionId`: The `all_sessions_default` path is explicitly documented bootstrap/debug behavior rather than a hidden bypass — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:70`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:174`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/status.ts:71`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:163:- Do NOT retry: Handler fallback without `sessionId`: The `all_sessions_default` path is explicitly documented bootstrap/debug behavior rather than a hidden bypass — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:70`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:174`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/status.ts:71`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:185:### Lifecycle transition persistence via reducer summaries: The reducer/test surfaces expose `lineageMode`, `generation`, and `sessionId`, but the inspected paths did not reveal any persisted `resumed`, `restarted`, `forked`, or `completed_continue` event handling. -- BLOCKED (iteration 7, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:186:- What was tried: Lifecycle transition persistence via reducer summaries: The reducer/test surfaces expose `lineageMode`, `generation`, and `sessionId`, but the inspected paths did not reveal any persisted `resumed`, `restarted`, `forked`, or `completed_continue` event handling.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:188:- Do NOT retry: Lifecycle transition persistence via reducer summaries: The reducer/test surfaces expose `lineageMode`, `generation`, and `sessionId`, but the inspected paths did not reveal any persisted `resumed`, `restarted`, `forked`, or `completed_continue` event handling.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:195:### Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:196:- What was tried: Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:198:- Do NOT retry: Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:220:### Reducer-owned graph/session dashboard fields: No new drift surfaced here because the reducer still exposes `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `graphConvergenceScore`, `graphDecision`, and `graphBlockers` consistently — `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:522-538` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:742-805` -- BLOCKED (iteration 4, 1 attempts)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:221:- What was tried: Reducer-owned graph/session dashboard fields: No new drift surfaced here because the reducer still exposes `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `graphConvergenceScore`, `graphDecision`, and `graphBlockers` consistently — `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:522-538` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:742-805`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:223:- Do NOT retry: Reducer-owned graph/session dashboard fields: No new drift surfaced here because the reducer still exposes `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `graphConvergenceScore`, `graphDecision`, and `graphBlockers` consistently — `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:522-538` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:742-805`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:263:| 002-semantic-coverage-graph | SQLite coverage graph: core + signals + contradictions + convergence + query + MCP handlers | mid 042 |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:69:  \\\"Phase 007-008 root spec vs phase spec alignment: cross-reference the root implementation-summary.md, spec.md, checklist.md, and tasks.md against all 8 phase implementation summaries. Check that Lane 1-5 remediation claims (REQ-026 through REQ-034) have actual code evidence.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:97:This bundle delivered runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across ~200 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research, sk-deep-review, and sk-improve-agent.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:124:Prior session context: A previous 10-iteration review (rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z) found 16 findings (0 P0 / 10 P1 / 6 P2) with CONDITIONAL verdict. That review led to a 5-lane remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034). This session validates the remediation AND examines areas not previously covered.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:145:sessionId: $SESSION_ID\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:172:  echo \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"iteration\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"run\\\\\\\":$i,\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"complete\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"focus\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$DIM — $(echo \\\"$FOCUS\\\" | head -c 80)\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"dimensions\\\\\\\":[\\\\\\\"$DIM\\\\\\\"],\\\\\\\"findingsCount\\\\\\\":$ITER_FINDINGS,\\\\\\\"findingsSummary\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"P0\\\\\\\":$ITER_P0,\\\\\\\"P1\\\\\\\":$ITER_P1,\\\\\\\"P2\\\\\\\":$ITER_P2},\\\\\\\"sessionId\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$SESSION_ID\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"generation\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"engine\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"codex-gpt-5.4-high-fast\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"startedAt\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$START_TS\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"completedAt\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$END_TS\\\\\\\"}\\\" >> \\\"$STATE_FILE\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/dispatch-20-iterations.sh:186:echo \\\"{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"dispatch_complete\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"mode\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"review\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"totalIterations\\\\\\\":$MAX_ITER,\\\\\\\"totalFindings\\\\\\\":$FINDINGS_TOTAL,\\\\\\\"activeP0\\\\\\\":$P0_TOTAL,\\\\\\\"activeP1\\\\\\\":$P1_TOTAL,\\\\\\\"activeP2\\\\\\\":$P2_TOTAL,\\\\\\\"engine\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"codex-gpt-5.4-high-fast\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"sessionId\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$SESSION_ID\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"timestamp\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)\\\\\\\"}\\\" >> \\\"$STATE_FILE\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:55:- v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation using the Phase 002 coverage graph once the graph surfaces are operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:87:- Add v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation that refines decomposition using the Phase 002 coverage graph once it is operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:91:- Define segment-local JSONL or state artifacts and deterministic merge rules into the main packet lineage using explicit keys: `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:147:| REQ-004 | Segment-local JSONL and merge rules MUST preserve auditability when wave results are merged back into the main packet lineage. | Segment artifacts remain replayable on their own, merged records always include explicit keys `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`, and merge logic never relies on append order as the source of truth. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:153:| REQ-005 | Each segment MUST use Phase 002 graph signals independently for convergence, pruning, promotion, and v2 decomposition upgrades. | Segment convergence explicitly references coverage-graph status or convergence outputs; prune logic can retire converged or stuck segments without dropping unresolved global gaps silently; graph-enhanced segmentation is blocked until the Phase 002 coverage graph is operational. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/001-runtime-truth-foundation/decision-record.md:553:| **Typed semantic decision trace** | Auditable, replayable, good debugging surface, supports future tuning | More schema fields and dashboard sections to maintain | 9/10 |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-020.md:7:- `SKILL.md` says resume replays the journal, coverage graph, and registry before dispatch and that the orchestrator skips mutation types already in the exhausted log, but the visible autonomous loop never invokes `mutation-coverage.cjs` before candidate generation. The shipped loop proceeds from integration scan directly to candidate generation, scoring, benchmarking, ledger append, reducer refresh, and reducer-driven stop check, so coverage state does not visibly steer mutation focus selection. (`.opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md:294-300`, `.opencode/commands/improve/assets/improve_agent-improver_auto.yaml:137-158`)\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-findings-registry.json:2:  \\\"sessionId\\\": \\\"rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-findings-registry.json:52:      \\\"description\\\": \\\"`coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges` key rows by bare `id` only (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:152-192`), and both upsert paths decide update vs insert with `WHERE id = ?` instead of the full namespace (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:370-376`). A later session that reuses an earlier node or edge ID mutates the existing row rather than creating a session-local record, violating REQ-012’s `specFolder + loopType + sessionId` isolation contract (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/008-further-deep-loop-improvements/spec.md:99-100`) and creating a cross-session overwrite/leak path underneath handlers that otherwise pass `sessionId`.\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-findings-registry.json:272:      \\\"description\\\": \\\"The research loop protocol still shows `{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"event\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"resumed\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"fromIteration\\\\\\\":N}` at `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/loop_protocol.md:83` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/loop_protocol.md:142`, while the review loop protocol only upgrades that example to `sessionId` / `generation` / `lineageMode` but still omits `timestamp` and the continuation fields at `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/loop_protocol.md:519-522`. The state-format references describe lifecycle events as first-class JSONL rows keyed by lineage metadata (`sessionId`, `continuedFromRun`, `timestamp`, and restart/fork ancestry fields) at `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md:240-243` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md:240-243`, and the quick references market these branches as live surfaces at `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/quick_reference.md:87-90` and `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/quick_reference.md:83`. Even if F010 is fixed later, these examples would still train operators toward under-specified lineage rows.\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:1:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"config\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"topic\\\":\\\"Further improvements to sk-deep-research v1.5.0.0, sk-deep-review v1.2.0.0, and sk-improve-agent v1.1.0.0 (and their associated commands, agents, YAML workflows): self-compliance audit, coverage graph integration audit, and prioritized recommendations.\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"rsr-2026-04-11T08-02-52Z\\\",\\\"parentSessionId\\\":null,\\\"lineageMode\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"generation\\\":1,\\\"continuedFromRun\\\":null,\\\"maxIterations\\\":20,\\\"convergenceThreshold\\\":0.05,\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-04-11T08:02:52Z\\\",\\\"specFolder\\\":\\\"skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2\\\"}\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:2:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"run\\\":1,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"D1 reducer rollup and resume drift\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":5,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":1.0,\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/loop_protocol.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/state_format.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/SKILL.md\\\",\\\".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_auto.yaml\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-research_confirm.yaml\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[\\\"D1: What undocumented edge cases, redundant reducer passes, journal-rollup gaps, or resume-flow drifts exist in the sk-deep-research v1.5.0.0 loop?\\\"],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-11T08:10:00Z\\\",\\\"durationMs\\\":420000,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"rsr-2026-04-11T08-02-52Z\\\",\\\"generation\\\":1,\\\"lineageMode\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"graphEvents\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"finding-reducer-event-drop\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Reducer drops non-iteration JSONL events\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"finding-stuck-dashboard-drift\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Dashboard stuck count under-reports low-ratio stalls\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"finding-rollup-schema-gap\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Reducer ignores noveltyJustification, structured ruledOut, sourceStrength, and graphEvents\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"finding-resume-ideas-gap\\\",\\\"label\\\":\