ucer reads only state ledger/config/mirror drift and never opens improvement-journal.jsonl\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-resume-contract-unexercised\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Visible auto and confirm workflows do not replay journals or propagate session lineage inputs\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-stop-surface-collapsed\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Operator-facing stop flow consumes reducer stopStatus booleans and free-text reasons rather than journal enums\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-no-visible-journal-emission\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-reducer-never-reads-journal\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-cli-doc-mismatch\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-no-visible-journal-emission\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-gateresults-not-enforced\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-no-visible-journal-emission\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"extends\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-reducer-never-reads-journal\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-stop-surface-collapsed\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-resume-contract-unexercised\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d4-upstream-stop-surface-collapsed\\\"}]}\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-state.jsonl:21:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"iteration\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"research\\\",\\\"run\\\":20,\\\"status\\\":\\\"complete\\\",\\\"focus\\\":\\\"D5 improve-agent coverage-graph operator-loop audit\\\",\\\"findingsCount\\\":5,\\\"newInfoRatio\\\":0.6,\\\"sourcesQueried\\\":[\\\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/deep-research-strategy.md\\\",\\\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-019.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/improve/agent.md\\\",\\\".opencode/commands/improve/assets/improve_agent-improver_auto.yaml\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/SKILL.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/assets/improvement_config.json\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/assets/improvement_strategy.md\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/mutation-coverage.cjs\\\",\\\".opencode/skills/sk-improve-agent/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\\\"],\\\"answeredQuestions\\\":[],\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-11T09:13:24Z\\\",\\\"durationMs\\\":180000,\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"rsr-2026-04-11T08-02-52Z\\\",\\\"generation\\\":1,\\\"lineageMode\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"graphEvents\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d5-improve-no-visible-focus-selection\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Visible improve-agent loop does not invoke coverage state before candidate generation, so graph data does not steer mutation focus\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d5-improve-configured-but-not-consumed\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Coverage graph is enabled in config and reserved in strategy placeholders but never read by the reducer\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d5-improve-helper-only-logic\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Mutation coverage helper records mutations and convergence eligibility but remains outside the visible command and reducer control path\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d5-improve-stop-gating-bypasses-graph\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"Visible stop decisions use ledger and reducer heuristics rather than coverage-graph convergence eligibility\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"node\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"d5-improve-no-visible-contradiction-gate\\\",\\\"label\\\":\\\"No contradiction-oriented graph gate appears in the published improve-agent operator path\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d5-improve-no-visible-focus-selection\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d5-improve-helper-only-logic\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d5-improve-configured-but-not-consumed\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d5-improve-stop-gating-bypasses-graph\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"extends\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d5-improve-helper-only-logic\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d5-improve-stop-gating-bypasses-graph\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"edge\\\",\\\"relation\\\":\\\"supports\\\",\\\"source\\\":\\\"d5-improve-stop-gating-bypasses-graph\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"d5-improve-no-visible-contradiction-gate\\\"}]}\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:65:- **Risk**: the coverage graph still mutates rows by bare ID, so two sessions reusing the same node or edge ID can overwrite each other.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:178:1. **REQ-026 [correctness] Claim adjudication must participate in legal STOP eligibility.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:184:3. **REQ-028 [security] Coverage-graph storage identity must be session-isolated under shared IDs.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:185:Coverage-graph writes must preserve `specFolder + loopType + sessionId + id` isolation semantics even when multiple sessions reuse the same node or edge ID.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:202:9. **REQ-034 [traceability] Release-readiness surfaces must not certify PASS while required review debt remains.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:210:REQ: REQ-026\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:220:REQ: REQ-028\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:260:REQ: REQ-034\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:265:REQ: REQ-034\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:296:| 2 | security session scoping on coverage graph runtime | security, traceability, maintainability | 0 | 1 | 1 | 0.40 | complete |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-003.md:28:| confirm_runtime | partial | soft | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_confirm.yaml:597` | The confirm mirrors preserve raw graph-event IDs and pass sessionId separately, so the namespace rule exists operationally but not in the payload contract authors are told to emit. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-003.md:40:- Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/plan.md:233:- **Safety Note**: Rollback must keep prepass artifacts and segment artifacts readable for debugging even when wave mode is disabled.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/plan.md:264:| Phase 3b graph-enhanced segmentation | Medium | Depends on Phase 002 coverage graph being operational and stable enough to refine v1 safely. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/001-runtime-truth-foundation/spec.md:46:| **Successor** | `../002-semantic-coverage-graph/spec.md` (Phase 002 — semantic coverage graph); downstream Phase 003 (wave executor), Phase 004 (offline loop optimizer) |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/001-runtime-truth-foundation/spec.md:89:- Broader operator-shell compression, guided bootstrap, or memory-platform redesign work from other research bundles unless it is directly required by the scoped runtime improvements in this packet.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:7:- The standalone graph helper does have bounded weight, not runaway influence: `computeGraphConvergence()` builds `graphScore` from fragmentation (0.25), normalized depth (0.25), question coverage (0.30), and source diversity (0.20), then limits the merged result to `blendedScore = compositeStop * 0.6 + graphScore * 0.4`. Inside this helper, the coverage graph cannot contribute more than 40% of the final blended scalar (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/lib/coverage-graph-convergence.cjs:141-205`).\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/research/iterations/iteration-014.md:10:- The shipped deep-review reducer mirrors the same pattern. `computeConvergenceScore()` reads `latest.convergenceSignals.compositeStop` or falls back to `1 - newFindingsRatio`, and the reducer then publishes only that scalar as `convergenceScore`. No inspected review reducer code reconstructs a coverage graph or invokes graph convergence logic before writing the dashboard/registry (`.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:360-390`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:579-583`, `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs:671-680`).\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:4:sessionId: rvw-2026-04-12T11-30-00Z\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:32:This bundle delivered runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across ~200 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research, sk-deep-review, and sk-improve-agent.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:59:Prior session context: A previous 10-iteration review (rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z) found 16 findings (0 P0 / 10 P1 / 6 P2) with CONDITIONAL verdict. That review led to a 5-lane remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034). This session validates the remediation AND examines areas not previously covered.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:70:/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \\\"042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2|rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z|REQ-026|REQ-034|wave-executor|wave-lifecycle|wave-segment-planner|wave-convergence\\\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/.codex/memories/MEMORY.md' in /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1259:- v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation using the Phase 002 coverage graph once the graph surfaces are operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1291:- Add v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation that refines decomposition using the Phase 002 coverage graph once it is operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1295:- Define segment-local JSONL or state artifacts and deterministic merge rules into the main packet lineage using explicit keys: `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1351:| REQ-004 | Segment-local JSONL and merge rules MUST preserve auditability when wave results are merged back into the main packet lineage. | Segment artifacts remain replayable on their own, merged records always include explicit keys `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`, and merge logic never relies on append order as the source of truth. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1357:| REQ-005 | Each segment MUST use Phase 002 graph signals independently for convergence, pruning, promotion, and v2 decomposition upgrades. | Segment convergence explicitly references coverage-graph status or convergence outputs; prune logic can retire converged or stuck segments without dropping unresolved global gaps silently; graph-enhanced segmentation is blocked until the Phase 002 coverage graph is operational. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1483:The JSONL merge contract uses explicit key ordering by `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId` rather than append order. Segment provenance, dedupe, and conflict metadata survive repeated merges. Segment JSONL lineage is deterministic and auditable.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1600:- **Risk**: the coverage graph still mutates rows by bare ID, so two sessions reusing the same node or edge ID can overwrite each other.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1713:1. **REQ-026 [correctness] Claim adjudication must participate in legal STOP eligibility.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1719:3. **REQ-028 [security] Coverage-graph storage identity must be session-isolated under shared IDs.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1720:Coverage-graph writes must preserve `specFolder + loopType + sessionId + id` isolation semantics even when multiple sessions reuse the same node or edge ID.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1737:9. **REQ-034 [traceability] Release-readiness surfaces must not certify PASS while required review debt remains.**\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1745:REQ: REQ-026\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1755:REQ: REQ-028\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1777:sessionId: rvw-2026-04-12T11-30-00Z\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1805:This bundle delivered runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across ~200 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research, sk-deep-review, and sk-improve-agent.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:1832:Prior session context: A previous 10-iteration review (rvw-2026-04-1