ing | -- | Stable identifier for the current review lineage |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4518:.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md:168:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"config\\\",\\\"mode\\\":\\\"review\\\",\\\"topic\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"reviewTarget\\\":\\\"...\\\",\\\"sessionId\\\":\\\"rvw-...\\\",\\\"parentSessionId\\\":null,\\\"lineageMode\\\":\\\"new\\\",\\\"generation\\\":1,\\\"continuedFromRun\\\":null,\\\"maxIterations\\\":7,\\\"convergenceThreshold\\\":0.10,\\\"createdAt\\\":\\\"2026-03-24T14:00:00Z\\\",\\\"specFolder\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4523:.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md:192:**Required fields:** `type`, `mode`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, `durationMs`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4525:.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md:201:| sessionId | string | Current lineage session identifier |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4583:   192\\t**Required fields:** `type`, `mode`, `run`, `status`, `focus`, `dimensions`, `filesReviewed`, `findingsCount`, `findingsSummary`, `findingsNew`, `newFindingsRatio`, `sessionId`, `generation`, `lineageMode`, `timestamp`, `durationMs`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4592:   201\\t| sessionId | string | Current lineage session identifier |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4607:    77\\t| lineage.sessionId | string | Yes | -- | Stable identifier for the current lineage segment |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4613:   240\\t| forked | workflow | active | Create a new branch from current packet state | sessionId, parentSessionId, generation, timestamp |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4614:   241\\t| completed_continue | workflow | active | Reopen a completed lineage after immutable snapshotting | sessionId, parentSessionId, generation, continuedFromRun, completedAt, reopenedAt, timestamp |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4704:6. **Convergence per segment**. Focus: whether each segment needs its own graph/coverage instance. Findings: convergence docs already say segment filtering should apply only to the current segment while hard stops still count all iterations and cross-segment analysis still reads the full JSONL ([convergence.md:23](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L23), [convergence.md:305](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L305)); the workers already expect the orchestrator to add `segment` and `convergenceSignals` to iteration records ([deep-research.md:189](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md#L189), [deep-review.md:253](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md#L253)); review STOP is explicitly global because it depends on total P0/P1 counts, full-dimension coverage, and global quality gates ([spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:340](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml#L340)). Novel insight: one global coverage graph plus segment-scoped queries is cleaner than spinning up a separate graph per segment. Open question: how should unresolved nodes from retired segments contribute to the final global stop-decision trace?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4720:- Normalize merge on explicit keys: `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, `run`, `findingId`. Never trust append order.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4752:6. **Convergence per segment**. Focus: whether each segment needs its own graph/coverage instance. Findings: convergence docs already say segment filtering should apply only to the current segment while hard stops still count all iterations and cross-segment analysis still reads the full JSONL ([convergence.md:23](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L23), [convergence.md:305](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L305)); the workers already expect the orchestrator to add `segment` and `convergenceSignals` to iteration records ([deep-research.md:189](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md#L189), [deep-review.md:253](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md#L253)); review STOP is explicitly global because it depends on total P0/P1 counts, full-dimension coverage, and global quality gates ([spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:340](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml#L340)). Novel insight: one global coverage graph plus segment-scoped queries is cleaner than spinning up a separate graph per segment. Open question: how should unresolved nodes from retired segments contribute to the final global stop-decision trace?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4768:- Normalize merge on explicit keys: `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, `run`, `findingId`. Never trust append order.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-002.md:19:- **F004**: Coverage-graph writes are not session-isolated when IDs collide — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154` — `coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges` key rows by bare `id` only (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:152-192`), and both upsert paths decide update vs insert with `WHERE id = ?` instead of the full namespace (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:370-376`). A later session that reuses an earlier node or edge ID mutates the existing row rather than creating a session-local record, violating REQ-012’s `specFolder + loopType + sessionId` isolation contract (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/008-further-deep-loop-improvements/spec.md:99-100`) and creating a cross-session overwrite/leak path underneath handlers that otherwise pass `sessionId`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-002.md:27:| spec_code | fail | hard | `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/008-further-deep-loop-improvements/spec.md:99` | REQ-012 requires shared graph helpers to scope by `specFolder + loopType + sessionId`, but the underlying write identity is still global by bare `id`. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-002.md:41:- Handler fallback without `sessionId`: The `all_sessions_default` path is explicitly documented bootstrap/debug behavior rather than a hidden bypass — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:70`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:174`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/status.ts:71`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/plan.md:3:description: \\\"Deliver the deep-loop coverage graph substrate by extracting shared graph primitives, adding dedicated storage and MCP tools, and wiring graph-backed convergence into deep research and deep review.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/plan.md:7:  - \\\"semantic coverage graph\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/plan.md:178:**Goal**: Surface the coverage graph through four stable MCP tools on the existing Spec Kit Memory MCP server.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/002-semantic-coverage-graph/plan.md:269:| Integration | SQLite bootstrap, schema rules, idempotent upsert, snapshot persistence | `coverage-graph-db.vitest.ts` |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:4:sessionId: rvw-2026-04-12T11-30-00Z\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:32:This bundle delivered runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across ~200 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research, sk-deep-review, and sk-improve-agent.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:59:Prior session context: A previous 10-iteration review (rvw-2026-04-11T13-50-06Z) found 16 findings (0 P0 / 10 P1 / 6 P2) with CONDITIONAL verdict. That review led to a 5-lane remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034). This session validates the remediation AND examines areas not previously covered.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:374:/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \\\"042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2|sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2|wave-coordination-board|wave-segment-state|optimizer-replay-corpus|optimizer-replay-runner|coverage graph|coverage-graph\\\" /Users/michelkerkmeester/.codex/memories/MEMORY.md' in /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:702:| `debug-delegation.md` | \\\"stuck\\\", \\\"can't fix\\\", \\\"tried everything\\\", \\\"same error\\\", \\\"fresh eyes\\\", \\\"hours on this\\\", \\\"still failing\\\", \\\"need help debugging\\\" | Suggest `/spec_kit:debug` |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:721:- `references/debugging/` for troubleshooting and root-cause methodology.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:796:        \\\"references/debugging/troubleshooting.md\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1371:/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \\\"wave-coordination-board|wave-segment-state|optimizer-replay-corpus|optimizer-replay-runner|coverage-graph|coverage graph\\\" .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/004-offline-loop-optimizer .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11' in /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1373:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:3:description: \\\"Four-phase implementation delivering runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across 100 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research and sk-deep-review.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1374:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/implementation-summary.md:60:Phases were delivered in strict dependency order: runtime truth first, then coverage graph, then wave execution, then offline optimization. The original four phases were independently validated against their task lists and quality gates.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1379:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:55:- v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation using the Phase 002 coverage graph once the graph surfaces are operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1380:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:87:- Add v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation that refines decomposition using the Phase 002 coverage graph once it is operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1384:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/spec.md:153:| REQ-005 | Each segment MUST use Phase 002 graph signals independently for convergence, pruning, promotion, and v2 decomposition upgrades. | Segment convergence explicitly references coverage-graph status or convergence outputs; prune logic can retire converged or stuck segments without dropping unresolved global gaps silently; graph-enhanced segmentation is blocked until the Phase 002 coverage graph is operational. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1393:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/plan.md:264:| Phase 3b graph-enhanced segmentation | Medium | Depends on Phase 002 coverage graph being operational and stable enough to refine v1 safely. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1405:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-002.md:19:- **F004**: Coverage-graph writes are not session-isolated when IDs collide — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154` — `coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges` key rows by bare `id` only (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:152-192`), and both upsert paths decide update vs insert with `WHERE id = ?` instead of the full namespace (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:370-376`). A later session that reuses an earlier node or edge ID mutates the existing row rather than creating a session-local record, violating REQ-012’s `specFolder + loopType + sessionId` isolation contract (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/008-further-deep-loop-improvements/spec.md:99-100`) and creating a cross-session overwrite/leak path underneath handlers that otherwise pass `sessionId`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1408:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-002.md:41:- Handler fallback without `sessionId`: The `all_sessions_default` path is explicitly documented bootstrap/debug behavior rather than a hidden bypass — `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/query.ts:70`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/convergence.ts:174`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/status.ts:71`\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1409:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:37:6. Convergence per segment: Each segment needs its own convergence assessment. Should each segment have its own coverage graph instance? Or one graph with segment-scoped queries?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1424:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4704:6. **Convergence per segment**. Focus: whether each segment needs its own graph/coverage instance. Findings: convergence docs already say segment filtering should apply only to the current segment while hard stops still count all iterations and cross-segment analysis still reads the full JSONL ([convergence.md:23](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L23), [convergence.md:305](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L305)); the workers already expect the orchestrator to add `segment` and `convergenceSignals` to iteration records ([deep-research.md:189](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md#L189), [deep-review.md:253](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md#L253)); review STOP is explicitly global because it depends on total P0/P1 counts, full-dimension coverage, and global quality gates ([spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:340](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml#L340)). Novel insight: one global coverage graph plus segment-scoped queries is cleaner than spinning up a separate graph per segment. Open question: how should unresolved nodes from retired segments contribute to the final global stop-decision trace?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1425:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/scratch/codex-gpt54-deep-research.md:4752:6. **Convergence per segment**. Focus: whether each segment needs its own graph/coverage instance. Findings: convergence docs already say segment filtering should apply only to the current segment while hard stops still count all iterations and cross-segment analysis still reads the full JSONL ([convergence.md:23](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L23), [convergence.md:305](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-deep-research/references/convergence.md#L305)); the workers already expect the orchestrator to add `segment` and `convergenceSignals` to iteration records ([deep-research.md:189](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-research.md#L189), [deep-review.md:253](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/agents/deep-review.md#L253)); review STOP is explicitly global because it depends on total P0/P1 counts, full-dimension coverage, and global quality gates ([spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:340](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml#L340)). Novel insight: one global coverage graph plus segment-scoped queries is cleaner than spinning up a separate graph per segment. Open question: how should unresolved nodes from retired segments contribute to the final global stop-decision trace?\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1428:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/iterations/iteration-003.md:40:- Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1429:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/003-wave-executor/tasks.md:66:- If Phase 002 coverage graph is not operational, block v2 graph-enhanced segmentation and stay on v1 heuristic planning.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1457:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-findings-registry.json:52:      \\\"description\\\": \\\"`coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges` key rows by bare `id` only (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:152-192`), and both upsert paths decide update vs insert with `WHERE id = ?` instead of the full namespace (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:370-376`). A later session that reuses an earlier node or edge ID mutates the existing row rather than creating a session-local record, violating REQ-012’s `specFolder + loopType + sessionId` isolation contract (`.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/008-further-deep-loop-improvements/spec.md:99-100`) and creating a cross-session overwrite/leak path underneath handlers that otherwise pass `sessionId`.\\\",\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.m