ew security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1476:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:198:- Do NOT retry: Looking for a second handler-side auth or validation bypass in `mcp_server/handlers/coverage-graph/upsert.ts`: the handler validates `specFolder`, `loopType`, `sessionId`, relation/kind enums, and self-loops, so this pass did not uncover a new security defect there beyond the pre-existing bare-ID storage semantics already captured in F004.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1477:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/deep-review-strategy.md:263:| 002-semantic-coverage-graph | SQLite coverage graph: core + signals + contradictions + convergence + query + MCP handlers | mid 042 |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1493:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:65:- **Risk**: the coverage graph still mutates rows by bare ID, so two sessions reusing the same node or edge ID can overwrite each other.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1497:.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/archive-rvw-2026-04-11/review-report.md:296:| 2 | security session scoping on coverage graph runtime | security, traceability, maintainability | 0 | 1 | 1 | 0.40 | complete |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1568:    55\\t- v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation using the Phase 002 coverage graph once the graph surfaces are operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1600:    87\\t- Add v2 graph/cluster-enhanced segmentation that refines decomposition using the Phase 002 coverage graph once it is operational.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1604:    91\\t- Define segment-local JSONL or state artifacts and deterministic merge rules into the main packet lineage using explicit keys: `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1660:   147\\t| REQ-004 | Segment-local JSONL and merge rules MUST preserve auditability when wave results are merged back into the main packet lineage. | Segment artifacts remain replayable on their own, merged records always include explicit keys `sessionId`, `generation`, `segment`, `wave`, and `findingId`, and merge logic never relies on append order as the source of truth. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1666:   153\\t| REQ-005 | Each segment MUST use Phase 002 graph signals independently for convergence, pruning, promotion, and v2 decomposition upgrades. | Segment convergence explicitly references coverage-graph status or convergence outputs; prune logic can retire converged or stuck segments without dropping unresolved global gaps silently; graph-enhanced segmentation is blocked until the Phase 002 coverage graph is operational. |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1758:     3\\tdescription: \\\"Four-phase implementation delivering runtime truth, semantic coverage graph, wave execution, and offline optimization across 100 files and +19K lines for sk-deep-research and sk-deep-review.\\\"\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1815:    60\\tPhases were delivered in strict dependency order: runtime truth first, then coverage graph, then wave execution, then offline optimization. The original four phases were independently validated against their task lists and quality gates.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1826:    71\\t1. **Lane 1 — Claim-Adjudication Stop Gate Wiring** closed F002 and F007 by adding a universal STOP veto pre-check and a dedicated `claimAdjudicationGate` in the review legal-stop decision tree, plus persisted `claim_adjudication` events, typed packet docs in `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md` §9, and matching `.opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/loop_protocol.md` §Step 4a. New REQs: REQ-026, REQ-027.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1827:    72\\t2. **Lane 2 — Coverage-Graph Session Isolation** closed F004, F005, F006, and F013 by bumping `deep-loop-graph.sqlite` to v2 with a composite primary key of `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` on both `coverage_nodes` and `coverage_edges`, migrating via drop-and-recreate, adding a shared-ID collisions regression to `session-isolation.vitest.ts`, and documenting the typed `graphEvents` payload shape and namespace rules in both state_format references. New REQs: REQ-028, REQ-029.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1830:    75\\t5. **Lane 5 — Release-Readiness Reconciliation** closed F013, F014, F015, and F016 by rewriting the phase-008 closeout surfaces, the packet-root completion surfaces below, and the reducer-owned `ACTIVE RISKS` dashboard section so non-P0 release-readiness debt stays visible. New REQ: REQ-034.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:1869:   114\\t| Closing-audit Lane 1–5 remediation (REQ-026 through REQ-034) | PASS — see `008-further-deep-loop-improvements/implementation-summary.md` §Closing Audit Remediation Notes and `review/review-report.md` |\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2162:    10\\t// always include explicit keys: sessionId, generation, segment,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2176:    24\\t  'sessionId',\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2214:    62\\t * @param {string} config.sessionId - Parent session identifier\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2226:    74\\t  if (!config || !isNonEmptyString(config.sessionId)) {\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2234:    82\\t    sessionId: config.sessionId,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2263:   111\\t * Every record includes sessionId, generation, segment, wave, and findingId.\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2279:   127\\t    sessionId: segmentState.sessionId,\\n.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/042-sk-deep-research-review-improvement-2/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:2289:   137\\t    s