.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/026-graph-and-context-optimization/007-code-graph/010-fix-iteration-quality-meta-research/review_archive/round-2-20260502T202250Z/iterations/iteration-005.md:18:R5 fix-completeness protocol was applied as `cross-consumer` plus `matrix/evidence`: the same-class producer inventory covers sk-code-review finding schema, the deep-review LEAF output contract, deep-review state schema, R7 review-report Planning Packet synthesis, R3 plan import/render prompts, and post-dispatch validation. The cross-consumer flow for a sample active finding is closed: `findingClass`/`scopeProof` are required by sk-code-review [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-code-review/references/review_core.md:82-88], produced by the deep-review agent [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md:152-184], carried by state `findingDetails` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-deep-review/references/state_format.md:195-219], synthesized into the R7 Planning Packet [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_deep-review_auto.yaml:1047-1055], and imported into the R3 FIX ADDENDUM body [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_plan_auto.yaml:215-229]. `scopeProofNeeded` has no live matches across the reviewed active surfaces.
