== 001/002/003 child tautology contexts ==
    52	
    53	### Problem Statement
    54	opencode's project-level skill discovery looks for `.opencode/skills/` (plural per `https://opencode.ai/docs/skills`). This repo uses `.opencode/skills/` (singular), so opencode's built-in discovery silently fails. Every `opencode run` dispatch prints "Could not find any skills directories" before falling through to the `opencode-skills` plugin's bridging behavior.
    55	
    56	### Purpose
    57	Rename `.opencode/skills/` → `.opencode/skills/` and update all 7,464 reference-bearing files in the repo. Patch 3 critical configs/scripts (opencode.json MCP commands, .claude/settings.local.json hooks, skill_advisor.py path lookups) that hard-code the singular path.
    58	<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->
    59	
    60	---
    61	
    62	<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->
    63	## 3. SCOPE
    64	
    65	### In Scope
    66	- `git mv .opencode/skill .opencode/skills` (preserves git history per file).
    67	- Bulk text replacement across 7,464 files / 645,862 occurrences.
    68	- Targeted patches: opencode.json (3 MCP refs), .claude/settings.local.json (4 hooks), skill_advisor.py (regex + dict keys + f-strings).
    69	- Per-phase verification: validate.sh strict, grep for residual singular refs, smoke-test opencode discovery.
    70	
    71	### Out of Scope
    72	- Renaming agent or command directories (Phases 002, 003).
    73	- Symlink redirects (Phase 004).
    74	- Modifying validate.sh / validate_document.py / generate-context.js (already use relative paths — confirmed safe).
    75	
    76	### Files to Change
    77	
    78	| File Path | Change Type | Description |
    79	|-----------|-------------|-------------|
    80	| `.opencode/skills/**` | Move | All 7,464 files moved to `.opencode/skills/**` via git mv |
    81	| `**/*.{md,json,jsonl,ts,js,sh,yaml,yml,py,tmpl,jsonc,tsx,mts}` | Modify | Bulk sed replacement of `.opencode/skills/` → `.opencode/skills/` |
    82	| `opencode.json` | Modify | 3 MCP server `command` arrays (lines 23, 44, 57) |
    83	| `.claude/settings.local.json` | Modify | 4 hook commands (lines 37, 49, 61, 73) |
    84	| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/skill_advisor/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | Modify | Regex + f-strings + dict keys |
    52	
    53	### Problem Statement
    54	opencode docs (`https://opencode.ai/docs/agents`) say project-level agent discovery looks for `.opencode/agents/` (plural). This repo uses `.opencode/agents/` (singular). 1,532 files reference the singular path including the CLAUDE.md §5 routing table and several JSON manifests with mirrorPath fields.
    55	
    56	### Purpose
    57	Rename `.opencode/agents/` → `.opencode/agents/` (12 agent files moved). Update all 1,532 reference-bearing files. Patch 4 critical configs (CLAUDE.md §5, sk-prompt graph-metadata mirrorPath, deep-research runtime_capabilities mirrorPath, audit_descriptions.py agent-half validators).
    58	<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->
    59	
    60	---
    61	
    62	<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->
    63	## 3. SCOPE
    64	
    65	### In Scope
    66	- `git mv .opencode/agent .opencode/agents`
   156	<!-- ANCHOR:edge-cases -->
   157	## L2: EDGE CASES
   158	
   159	### Data Boundaries
   160	- TOML files in `.codex/agents/`: bulk sed string match works regardless of format.
   161	- mirrorPath JSON values: sed catches `.opencode/agents/<name>` → `.opencode/agents/<name>`.
   162	
   163	### Error Scenarios
   164	- audit_descriptions.py validator regex breaks: orchestrator fixes manually.
    52	
    53	### Problem Statement
    54	opencode docs (`https://opencode.ai/docs/commands`) say project-level command discovery looks for `.opencode/commands/` (plural). Repo uses singular. 1,811 files reference the singular path; `audit_descriptions.py` validates `.opencode/commands/**` paths; `target_manifest.jsonc` and `mcp-doctor.sh` have hardcoded paths.
    55	
    56	### Purpose
    57	Rename `.opencode/commands/` → `.opencode/commands/` (69 files across 6 subdirs moved). Update 1,811 reference-bearing files. Patch 3 critical files.
    58	<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->
